# Brand Voice and Language Rules

## Intent
Enforce a unified, trauma-informed brand language across ctf/, landing-page/, waitlist-landing-page/, and wiki-blog/.

## Source of Truth
- Canonical language reference: `ctf/docs/BRAND_VOICE_LEXICON.md`.
- For any wording conflict, this module defers to the lexicon.

## Required Read Order For Copy Work
- Read `index.mdc`.
- Read this file.
- Read `ctf/docs/BRAND_VOICE_LEXICON.md` before editing user-facing copy.

## Brand Identity Rules
- Use Charging the Future as the organization and umbrella brand.
- Use TI Skills Economy as the product name.
- Use Psyop-Free Economy as positioning language, not as a replacement product name.

## Terminology Rules
- Default to survivors, not victims, except in legal/statutory contexts.
- Replace gang stalking and gang stalker with Specterati terminology where applicable.
- Do not refer to chat as a standalone product; use plugin-context naming (for example Chyme chat).

## Specterati Placement Rules
- Tier 1 Editorial and explanatory content: full lexicon allowed.
- Tier 2 Contextual UI support text: only explanatory use.
- Tier 3 Restricted contexts: CTA labels, error messages, placeholders, and accessibility labels.

## Voice Rules
- Keep copy calm, plain, and predictable.
- Avoid stigmatizing, sensational, coercive, or manipulative framing.
- Prefer specific product behavior statements over abstract hype language.

## Pre-Merge Copy Audit Checklist
- Search for `gang stalk|gang stalking` in changed copy files.
- Search for `\bvictim(s)?\b` in changed copy files and validate legal/statutory exception.
- Search for standalone `chat` labels and ensure plugin context naming.
- Validate terms against `ctf/docs/BRAND_VOICE_LEXICON.md`.

## Release Constraint
Any user-facing copy change in ctf/, landing-page/, waitlist-landing-page/, or wiki-blog/ is blocked from release until this module and the lexicon are satisfied.
